# Elsewhere — Environment

## Single site + single Supabase (required)

Create **one** Supabase project. Put these on **this** Next app only
(Vercel project root = `apps/web`). Marketing (`/`) and product (`/app`, `/start`)
share the same origin and the same users.

```bash
# App URL — used for auth redirects / absolute links
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=http://localhost:3000

# Supabase — ONE project for the whole brand
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=

# Newsletter (Corridor Brief) — prefer Resend; webhook optional
RESEND_API_KEY=
RESEND_FROM_EMAIL=Elsewhere <hello@elsewhereplan.com>
RESEND_AUDIENCE_ID=
NEWSLETTER_WEBHOOK=
# Legacy alias still accepted by /api/newsletter:
WAITLIST_WEBHOOK=

# Analytics (later)
NEXT_PUBLIC_POSTHOG_KEY=
NEXT_PUBLIC_POSTHOG_HOST=https://app.posthog.com
```

### Docs

- Auth topology: `docs/plans/ONE_SITE_ONE_AUTH.md`
- Email + paid digest + YOUR checklist: `docs/plans/EMAIL_AND_SUPABASE.md`

### Supabase Auth redirect allowlist

Add every hostname that will run this app (not a second Vite app):

- `http://localhost:3000/**`
- `https://YOUR_VERCEL_HOST/**`
- production domain when live

Do **not** create a second Supabase project for the old Vite landing.
